line_1: To thrust the charge of deeds that I detest,
The specious arts of vice detest.
line_2: With early virtues plant your breast,
You, Feaver, Gout, and all the rest,

line_1: This and Fox-Hunting, th' Ancients did detest,
line_2: Where you Ride ten or twenty Miles at least,

line_1: May we the latent ills detest,
For scorning what they taught him to detest.
line_2: Died by the sentence of a shaven priest,

line_1: But from my soul all scandal I detest,
line_2: Truth forms my numbers, as she warms my breast,
